			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2025</a> paper:</span><br><i>Detecting Resource Leaks on Android with Alpakka</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/GustavoSoaresSantos.html">Gustavo Soares Santos</a>, <a href="../profile/JoãoBispo.html">João Bispo</a>, <a href="../profile/AlexandraMendes.html">Alexandra Mendes</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3732771.3742724">10.1145/3732771.3742724</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagM">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Alpakka is a source-to-source compiler over Smali that transforms programs to detect and repair resource leaks.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> Automatically localizing and fixing resource leaks supports maintenance and regression prevention in Android apps.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports an empirical evaluation on a dataset of real APKs and quantifies findings such as false positive rates.
</li></ul></li></ul>
